In [[civil procedure]] a '''penal notice''' is a warning endorsed on a [[court order]], notifying the recipient that he or she is liable to committal to prison or to pay a [[Fine (penalty)|fine]] for breach of the order.  In the case of a [[company]] or [[corporation]], their [[asset]]s may be [[Seisin|seized]].{{Sfn|UK Civil Procedure Rules: 9.1}}{{Sfn|Civil Procedure|2001|p=498}}

